## The Movista API
**Version:** 2.1

This API allows your company to create programs to interact directly with data gathered by Movista as well as setup work for Reps automatically.
# **MVID Identifier**
MVID is the unique identifier used in the system. Some legacy application may have integrated with ExternalID, so that value is returned to match MVID. Any path variables or data related directly the ID values should reference MVID. 

 In a GET response, MVID will be returned at the top level and the Data element will have information about the requested endpoint. 

 In a POST request, MVID can be included inside the Data element to set it to a specific value. Otherwise, an auto-generated value will be used.
# **User Stories**
These stories explain some more common tasks that require calls to multiple endpoints one after the other, passing data from one to the next.
## Setup User Story Required Data
To use the stories below, there is some prep work needed to create some data elements so **start here**
1. Create Role - create the needed Roles in the system [Roles/createRole](?urls.primaryName=Roles#/Role/createRole)
2. Create Retailer - create the Retailer groupings the Reps service [Locations/Retailer/createRetailer](?urls.primaryName=Locations#/Retailer/createRetailer)
3. Create Locations - create the individual Locations that link to the Retailers above [Locations/createLocation](?urls.primaryName=Locations#/Location/createLocation)
4. Create Sample Items - create the items needed in Item Master or mPlans [Item/createItem](?urls.primaryName=Item%20Manager#/Item/createItem)
5. Create Item Set - create an itemset to link together the items by MVID [Item/createItemSet](?urls.primaryName=Item%20Manager#/Item/createItemSet)
## Create Simple mPlan
1. Create mPlan - start by creating an mPlan to link information to [mPlans/mPlan/createmPlan](?urls.primaryName=mPlans#/mPlan/createmPlan)
2. Add Assignments - create a few batch assignments to link the mPlan to a brand and some stores [Assignments/createAssignment](?urls.primaryName=Assignments#/Assignment/createAssignment)
3. Add Base Request - add a base request to the mPlan to link target requests to [mPlans/Request/createRequest](?urls.primaryName=mPlans#/Request/createRequest)
4. Add mPlan's Target Request - add a detailed target request and reference the MVID of the base request created above [mPlans/Request/createTargetRequest](?urls.primaryName=mPlans#/Request/createTargetRequest)
## Delete Simple mPlan
If you need to delete an mPlan, the steps need to be done in reverse order to creating the mPlan
1. Delete Target Request - remove the target request for the mPlan in question [mPlans/Request/deleteTargetRequest](?urls.primaryName=mPlans#/Request/deleteTargetRequest)
2. Delete Base Request - remove the base request once the target request is no longer linked [mPlans/Request/deleteRequest](?urls.primaryName=mPlans#/Request/deleteRequest)
3. Delete Assignments - remove any assignments to the mPlan [Assignment/deleteAssignment](?urls.primaryName=Assignments#/Assignment/deleteAssignment)
4. Delete mPlan - remove the top level mPlan you are deleting [mPlans/mPlan/deletemPlan](?urls.primaryName=mPlans#/mPlan/deletemPlan)
# **Batch API Information**
To simplify creating and modifying large amounts of information, Movista API includes batch processing. More details about the types of API calls accepted and how to format properly is provided here - [Batch API Information](?urls.primaryName=Batch%20API%20Information)
# **API Error Codes and Messages**
If there is an error with an API call, the HTTP response code will show up in the 4** range, but specific details about what the error was will come back in the response body as an error code and message. Details about the various errors are here - [API Error Codes and Messages](?urls.primaryName=API%20Error%20Codes%20and%20Messages)
# **Table of Contents**
API endpoints are grouped by the part of the API / application they are related to. In order to see an alphabetical listing of endpoints (and the API they related to), check here - [Endpoint Table of Contents](?urls.primaryName=Endpoint%20Table%20of%20Contents)

## Batch API Information
**Version:** 2.1

To use batch API, change the URL from /api/{endpoint} to /api/batch/{endpoint}. 

 The payload sent to the batch API is the same as for a single call except it should be structured as an array of entries. 

 Batch API calls only work for POST or PUT on Resource endpoints. 

 The Response from batch API calls include *errors* and *processed* which are each arrays of the individual Resource response - formatted like the schema example below

**Base URL(s):**
- `https://{subdomain}.mvretail.com/api/batch/`


### Component Schemas


#### ResponseBatch

Type: object

## API Error Codes and Messages
**Version:** 2.1

Some response codes like 400 or 404 are used for a variety of error messages. Below are examples of error codes and associated messages for reference. 

 2001 - Unsupported action type {HttpMethod}
 2003 - Malformed request payload
 2005 - This endpoint does not allow {HttpMethod} requests.
 2009 - This endpoint is currently in use by another process
 3106 - Invalid resource reference - invalid reference object on {FieldName}
 3107 - Resource not found
 3108 - A record already exists for that ID {IDs}
 3109 - A record already exists for {FieldName} ({Value})
 3110 - Invalid resource type {Type}
 3112 - No identifier fields supplied 

 Responses that contain these errors will be formatted like the schema example below


### Component Schemas


#### ResponseError

Type: object

## Assignments
**Version:** 2.1

# **Overview**
The Assignments API allows you to add, edit, retrieve and delete Assignments in your Movista application environment.
* Viewing Assignments - call GET method with an MVID to view data about a single Assignment linkage
* Creating Assignments - create a new assignment linking by calling POST method with the Type / Value of assignment as well as AssociatedObject this assignment is related to. In creation, the apiDefaultUser or domain admin will be used for the OwnerObject.
* Updating Assignments - modify an existing Assignment by calling PUT method with the MVID of the assignment to modify in the path and any updated Type / Valie or AssociatedObject information.
* Deleting Assignments - Provide the MVID of the Assignment to delete in the path and call DELETE method

**Base URL(s):**
- `https://{subdomain}.mvretail.com/api/`

**Available Tags:**
- **Assignment**: Information related to Assignments

### Endpoints

#### POST `/assignment`
**Operation ID:** createAssignment
**Tags:** Assignment
**Summary:** Create a new Assignment - Without OwnerObject user information to use default user

**Parameters:**
None

**Request Body:**
  Content-Type: application/json
  Schema: Combined from: MVIDOnly, AssignmentNoOwnerObject

**Responses:**
  - **200**: OK
  - **400**: No description

---

#### GET `/assignment/{AssignmentID}`
**Operation ID:** getAssignmentByID
**Tags:** Assignment
**Summary:** Get Assignment by AssignmentID

**Parameters:**
  - **AssignmentID** [path] (string) (required)
    MVID of the record to retrieve

**Responses:**
  - **200**: OK
  - **400**: No description
  - **404**: No description

---

#### PUT `/assignment/{AssignmentID}`
**Operation ID:** updateAssignment
**Tags:** Assignment
**Summary:** Update an existing Assignment

**Parameters:**
  - **AssignmentID** [path] (string) (required)
    MVID of the Assignment to update

**Request Body:**
  Content-Type: application/json
  Schema:  Assignment

**Responses:**
  - **200**: OK
  - **400**: No description
  - **404**: No description

---

#### DELETE `/assignment/{AssignmentID}`
**Operation ID:** deleteAssignment
**Tags:** Assignment
**Summary:** Delete an existing Assignment

**Parameters:**
  - **AssignmentID** [path] (string) (required)
    MVID of Assignment to delete

**Responses:**
  - **204**: No description
  - **400**: No description
  - **404**: No description

---

## Item Manager
**Version:** 2.1

# **Overview**
Information about Item Manager API
# **Changelog**
## Version 2.1
* In this version the documentation was standardized

**Base URL(s):**
- `https://{subdomain}.mvretail.com/api`

**Available Tags:**
- **ItemLevel**: Points of entry to be used within the Item Manager hierarchy
- **ItemLevelOverride**: Defines the relationships between ItemLevels and authorizes or deauthorizes them for particular Loca
- **Item**: Items used within the Item Manager
- **ItemOverride**: Authorizes or deauthorizes Item(s) for one or more ItemLevelOverrides
- **ItemActionInstance**: Instances of ItemActions (Orders, Returns, and Audits) and their attributes
- **ItemRow**: Relates an Item to an ItemActionInstance including quantity and any additional attributes
- **Field**: Associates attributes of Items, ItemRows, and ItemActionInstances with Forms and Templates
- **Form**: A collection of Fields to gather details about an ItemActionInstance
- **Template**: A collection of Fields to display attributes for Items, ItemRows, or ItemActionInstances within a gi
- **Image**: A photo of an Item

## Locations
**Version:** 2.1

# **Overview**
The Locations API allows you to add, edit, list and delete retail locations and other groupings and attributes related to it.
## Location, Retailer and LocationLists
* **Location**  A Location represents any single retail space where work can be done. An example is 'Walmart Store 100'. A location can have CustomFields assigned to it for attribution purposes.
* **Retailer**  A classification for Location that groups individual locations together into the banner they fall within. An example is 'Walmart'
* **LocationList**  A grouping of locations for assignment or reporting. An example is 'All store in Western Texas'. A location list can contain locations that are part of different retailers. Also, a single location can be in multiple location lists.
* **CustomField**  A method of general attribution for locations.
# **Changelog**
## Version 2.1
* In this version the documentation was standardized

**Base URL(s):**
- `https://{subdomain}.mvretail.com/api`

**Available Tags:**
- **Location**: Information about individual Locations
- **Retailer**: Information about retailer
- **LocationList**: Information about LocationList groupings
- **CustomField**: Information about CustomField attribution

## mPlans
**Version:** 2.1

# Overview
 
The mPlan API allows you to review, add, edit and delete mPlans and the data structures related to mPlans in your Movista environment.
 
## mPlan Object Definitions
 
* **mPlan**  A project plan for a unit of work in your Movista environment.
 
* **HotTask**  A short (no more than 3 question) project plan for an urgent task in your Movista environment.
 
* **File** - A file used for reference to link with an mPlan.
* **Request**  An individual question or other instruction in an mPlan.
* **TargetRequest**  The attachment of a Request to an mPlan.
* **TargetRequestSet**
* **PossibleResponse**  A single multiple-choice answer for a Request.
* **TargetPossibleResponse**  The attachment of a Possible Response to a Request.
* **RequestItemContext**   The definition of a set of Items to be referenced by an mPlan.
* **TargetRequestItemContext**  The attachment of a Request Item Context to a specific mPlan.
* **LocationTargetRequestItemContext**
* **mPlanLocationOverride**
* **Staffing**
* **TagName**
* **TagValue**
* **Image**
# Changelog
 
## Version 2.1
* In this version the documentation was standardized

**Base URL(s):**
- `https://{subdomain}.mvretail.com/api/`

**Available Tags:**
- **mPlan**: Information about mPlan definitions
- **HotTask**: Information about HotTask definitions
- **File**: Information about Files to link with mPlans
- **Request**: Information about Requests
- **PossibleResponse**: Information about PossibleResponses
- **RequestItemContext**: Information about RequestItemContexts
- **mPlanLocationOverride**: Information about mPlanLocationOverrides
- **Staffing**: Information about Action endpoints for Staffing
- **mPlan Tags**: Information about TagNames and TagValues for mPlans
- **Image**: Information about Images

## Reps
**Version:** 2.1

# **Overview**
The Reps API allows you to add, edit, activate and and deactivate Reps and RepTypes from your Movista environment.
## Reps vs. RepTypes
* **Reps**  A Rep is a individual who performs work in-store using the Movista mobile app.
* **RepType**  A classification for Reps or a type of rep who works in Store. For example, a rep could have a RepType of Merchandiser or Demonstrator, or both.
## Rep
* Viewing RepTypes - call GET method with an MVID to view data about a single Rep or if you have AuthN enabled and enfored without MVID to see a list of all Reps
* Creating Reps - Provide the request body Data element of the Rep as described below and call POST method. Create the RepTypes and TimeManager Users first before you create a Rep that associates to those.
* Updating Reps - Provide the MVID of the Rep to update in the path and the request body Data element as described below and call PUT method. To Activate or Deactivate a Rep, call PUT method and in Data just provide true / false for Active flag
* Deleting Reps - Provide the MVID of the Rep to delete in the path and call DELETE method
## RepType
* Viewing RepTypes - call GET method with either an MVID to view data about a single RepType or without MVID to see a list of all RepTypes
* Creating RepTypes - Provide the request body Data element of the RepType as described below and call POST method
* Updating RepTypes - Provide the MVID of the RepType to update in the path and the request body Data element as described below and call PUT method
* Deleting RepTypes - Provide the MVID of the RepType to delete in the path and call DELETE method

## Scheduling
**Version:** 2.1

# **Overview**
Scheduling provides information about a Rep's calendar feature that shows availability and planned up coming mPlan work. This single endpoint interacts with information about ScheduledEvent, ScheduledAvailability, ScheduledLocation and ScheduledmPlan. Based on which Type is specified for each MVID, the Data will be returned differently.
## Data provided for each Type
Though there is a single endpoint, the format of the data expected vaires, so the Schemas / Models listing at the bottom contains a schema for each Type
### ScheduledEvent
Data includes Start and End timestamps and Notes
### ScheduledAvailability
Data includes Start and End timestamps and Notes then also has Rep which is a Reference of Type "Rep" and MVID
### ScheduledLocation
Data includes Start and End timestamps and Notes then also has Rep which is a Reference of Type "Rep" and MVID. This also has a Location which is a Reference of Type "Location" and MVID.
### ScheduledmPlan
Data includes Start and End timestamps and Notes then also has Rep which is a Reference of Type "Rep" and MVID. This also has a Location which is a Reference of Type "Location" and MVID. This also has an mPlan which is a Reference of Type "mPlan" and MVID.

## Users
**Version:** 2.1

# **Overview**
The Users API allows you to add, edit, activate and and deactivate Users and Usergroups from your Movista environment. These are Users of the Portal application (note this is different from Reps who are using the mobile app).,
## Users vs. Usergroups
* **Users**  A User is a individual who works uses the Movista Portal (website) application to create mPlans and perform other administrative functions that can be pushed down to Reps working in stores.
* **Usergroups**  A classification for Reps or a type of rep that works in Store. For example, a rep could have a RepType of Merchandiser or Demonstrator, or both.
## Users
* Viewing RepTypes - call GET method with an MVID to view data about a single Rep or if you have AuthN enabled and enfored without MVID to see a list of all Reps
* Creating Reps - Provide the request body Data element of the Rep as described below and call POST method. Create the RepTypes and TimeManager Users first before you create a Rep that associates to those.
* Updating Reps - Provide the MVID of the Rep to update in the path and the request body Data element as described below and call PUT method. To Activate or Deactivate a Rep, call PUT method and in Data just provide true / false for Active flag
* Deleting Reps - Provide the MVID of the Rep to delete in the path and call DELETE method
## Usergroups
Usergroups define the access and authority your administrative users have when accessing their administrative portal. You should set up Usergroups prior to creating your first set of administrative Users.
* Viewing RepTypes - call GET method with either an MVID to view data about a single RepType or without MVID to see a list of all RepTypes
* Creating RepTypes - Provide the request body Data element of the RepType as described below and call POST method
* Updating RepTypes - Provide the MVID of the RepType to update in the path and the request body Data element as described below and call PUT method
* Deleting RepTypes - Provide the MVID of the RepType to delete in the path and call DELETE method
